			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: The MITRE CVE dictionary describes this issue as: Libgcrypt before 1.7.10 and 1.8.x before 1.8.3 allows a memory-cache side-channel attack on ECDSA signatures that can be mitigated through the use of blinding during the signing process in the _gcry_ecc_ecdsa_sign function in cipher/ecc-ecdsa.c, aka the Return Of the Hidden Number Problem or ROHNP. To discover an ECDSA key, the attacker needs access to either the local machine or a different virtual machine on the same physical host. \n            STATEMENT: Since the 5.8.3 release, Red Hat CloudForms no longer uses libtomcrypt.",
